Granting All Privileges
Command from Image
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES
ON database_name.*
TO 'admin_user'@'localhost';
Simple Meaning

Give all permissions to the user.

User can now:

SELECT → View data
INSERT → Add data
UPDATE → Modify data
DELETE → Remove data
CREATE → Create tables
DROP → Delete tables
Real Example
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES
ON practice_db.*
TO 'admin1'@'localhost';
Before GRANT
User	Permissions
admin1	No access
After GRANT
User	Permissions
admin1	Full access to practice_db
Example Table Access
students table
student_id	name
1	Arun
2	Ravi
Before GRANT

User admin1:

❌ Cannot see table
❌ Cannot insert data
❌ Cannot delete data

After GRANT

User admin1 can:

SELECT * FROM students;

INSERT INTO students VALUES (3, 'Priya');

DELETE FROM students WHERE student_id = 2;

